		"text"		: "1\n00:00:02,580 --> 00:00:07,460\n--Hi. I'm Tia Mowry.\n--And I'm Tamera Mowry from \"Sister, Sister.\"\n\n2\n00:00:07,460 --> 00:00:10,719\nWelcome to the Screen Actors Guild Foundation BookPALS.\n\n3\n00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:15,560\nAnd today, we're going to be reading \"No Mirrors in my Nana's House.\"\n\n4\n00:00:15,860 --> 00:00:23,140\nYou know, Tamera, when I was first introduced to this book, I was very intrigued by the title, \"No Mirrors in My Nana's House\"\n\n5\n00:00:23,140 --> 00:00:30,440\nand I actually, you know, had to ask myself, how would this world, or how would our society actually be without any mirrors?\n\n6\n00:00:30,440 --> 00:00:33,400\nI mean, would there be any stereotypes?\n\n7\n00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:42,720\nI liked the book because I thought it sounded like a song and it kind of had a wonderful rhythm to it. So I'm very excited.\n\n8\n00:00:42,720 --> 00:00:45,240\nI think it's very colorful and fun.\n\n9\n00:00:45,240 --> 00:00:56,060\nThe author of the book is Ysaye Barnwell and the illustrations and paintings are by Synthia Saint James.\n\n10\n00:00:56,060 --> 00:00:59,140\nThere were no mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n11\n00:00:59,140 --> 00:01:02,640\nNo mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n12\n00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:05,340\nSo the beauty that I saw in everything\n\n13\n00:01:05,340 --> 00:01:07,560\nThe beauty in everything\n\n14\n00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:12,440\nWas in her eyes like the rising of the sun.\n\n15\n00:01:13,160 --> 00:01:15,960\nThere were no mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n16\n00:01:15,960 --> 00:01:18,390\nNo mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n17\n00:01:18,390 --> 00:01:22,080\nSo I never knew that my skin was too black\n\n18\n00:01:22,080 --> 00:01:26,480\nI never knew that my nose was too flat\n\n19\n00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:29,490\nI never knew that my clothes didn't fit\n\n20\n00:01:29,490 --> 00:01:33,540\nI never knew there were things that I missed\n\n21\n00:01:33,540 --> 00:01:38,860\n'Cause the beauty in everything was in her eyes\n\n22\n00:01:38,860 --> 00:01:42,240\nLike the rising of the sun.\n\n23\n00:01:42,660 --> 00:01:45,300\nThere were no mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n24\n00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:47,720\nNo mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n25\n00:01:47,720 --> 00:01:50,820\nI was intrigued by the cracks in the wall\n\n26\n00:01:50,820 --> 00:01:55,260\nI tasted with joy the dust that would fall\n\n27\n00:01:55,260 --> 00:01:59,240\nThe noise in the hallway was music to me\n\n28\n00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:03,600\nThe trash and the rubbish just cushioned my feet\n\n29\n00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:07,440\nAnd the beauty in everything was in her eyes,\n\n30\n00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:11,840\nlike the rising of the sun was in her eyes.\n\n31\n00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:16,160\nThere were no mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n32\n00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:18,460\nNo mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n33\n00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:21,860\nThe world outside was a magical place\n\n34\n00:02:21,860 --> 00:02:25,499\nI only knew love and I never knew hate\n\n35\n00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:29,660\nAnd the beauty in everything was in her eyes\n\n36\n00:02:29,660 --> 00:02:32,900\nlike the rising of the sun\n\n37\n00:02:33,340 --> 00:02:44,020\nChil', look deep into my eyes\n\n38\n00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:50,400\nRemember in the beginning when I told you this book reminded me of a song?\n\n39\n00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:52,880\nActually, it was inspired by a song.\n\n40\n00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:58,200\nAnd you know the author, Ysaye Barnwell, she's in a group called \"Sweet Honey and the Rock.\"\n\n41\n00:02:58,200 --> 00:03:03,240\nAnd now, we get to listen to them sing: \"No Mirrors in My Nana's House.\"\n\n42\n00:03:03,580 --> 00:03:09,440\nThere were no mirrors in my Nana's house\nNo mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n43\n00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:16,200\nThere were no mirrors in my Nana's house\nNo mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n44\n00:03:16,420 --> 00:03:22,120\nAnd the beauty that I saw in everything\nThe beauty in everything\n\n45\n00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:28,740\nYeah, was in her eyes\nLike the rising of the sun\n\n46\n00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:36,380\nI'm telling you, there were no mirrors in my Nana's house\nNo mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n47\n00:03:36,660 --> 00:03:43,020\nThere were no mirrors in my Nana's house\nNo mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n48\n00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:46,200\nI never knew that my skin was too black\n\n49\n00:03:46,340 --> 00:03:49,400\nAnd I never knew that my nose was too flat\n\n50\n00:03:49,580 --> 00:03:52,660\nAnd I never knew that my clothes didn't fit\n\n51\n00:03:52,740 --> 00:03:55,820\nAnd I never knew there were things that I'd missed\n\n52\n00:03:55,820 --> 00:04:00,900\n'Cause the beauty in everything, yeah\nWas in her eyes\n\n53\n00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:04,940\nLike the rising of the sun was in her eyes\n\n54\n00:04:05,220 --> 00:04:12,760\nOh, there were no mirrors in my Nana's house\nNo mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n55\n00:04:12,820 --> 00:04:19,440\nThere were no mirrors in my Nana's house\nNo mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n56\n00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:22,560\nI was intrigued by the cracks in the wall\n\n57\n00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:25,420\nThe dust in the sun looked like snow that would fall\n\n58\n00:04:25,780 --> 00:04:29,020\nThe noise in the hallway was music to me\n\n59\n00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:32,160\nThe trash and the rubbish would cushion my feet\n\n60\n00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:37,220\nAnd the beauty in everything\nWas in her eyes\n\n61\n00:04:37,220 --> 00:04:41,560\nLike the rising of the sun was in her eyes\n\n62\n00:04:42,660 --> 00:04:49,360\nThere were no mirrors in my Nana's house\nNo mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n63\n00:04:49,420 --> 00:04:55,720\nThere were no mirrors in my Nana's house\nNo mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n64\n00:04:55,940 --> 00:04:59,100\nThe world outside was a magical place\n\n65\n00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:02,220\nI only knew love and I didn't know hate\n\n66\n00:05:02,220 --> 00:05:07,220\nAnd the beauty in everything, yeah\nWas in her eyes\n\n67\n00:05:07,220 --> 00:05:11,880\nLike the rising of the sun was in her eyes\n\n68\n00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:19,260\nThere were no mirrors in my Nana's house\nNo mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n69\n00:05:19,280 --> 00:05:25,360\nThere were no mirrors in my Nana's house\nNo mirrors in my Nana's house\n\n70\n00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:31,280\nAnd the beauty that I saw in everything\nThe beauty in everything, yeah\n\n71\n00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:38,780\nWas in her eyes\nLike the rising of the sun was in her eyes\n\n72\n00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:59,200\nChil', look deep into my eyes\n\n73\n00:05:59,220 --> 00:06:06,160\n--Wow, that was incredible. That was beautiful.\n--I loved it.\n\n74\n00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:09,540\nYou know what, in a way, it made the book come alive to me.\n\n75\n00:06:09,540 --> 00:06:11,820\n--Yeah. It really did. If you're reading it--\n--It touches you.\n\n76\n00:06:11,820 --> 00:06:14,760\nMm-hmm, right here, in the heart, in the soul, it was very beautiful.\n\n77\n00:06:14,760 --> 00:06:19,740\nWell, I enjoyed it. I hope you guys did too, and thanks for watching.\n\n78\n00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:20,260\nBye!",
